<ul class="bullets">
	<li>AoS/AoC: Philosophy of Science</li>
	<li>Deadline: 16 April 2010; interviews in early May</li>
</ul>
<p>
The Department of Science and Technology Studies at UCL seeks to appoint a
full-time Lecturer in Philosophy of Science, with teaching and research
interests in the philosophy of science, and - preferably - the history and
philosophy of the physical sciences broadly construed. The successful
applicant must hold a PhD in the appropriate subject area, and is expected
to have a range of interests within history and philosophy of science, to
be active in research and publication, and to be capable of teaching the
subject to undergraduate and postgraduate students from a wide range of
backgrounds.
